 SAI to host roller hockey
A STAFF REPORTERCalcutta: The Sports Authority of India (SAI) Eastern Centre will host the 12th Asian roller hockey and roller inline hockey championships from November 28-December 2. As of now, eight countries  China, Iran, Pakistan, Macau, Chinese Taipei, Hong Kong, Japan and India  have already confirmed their participation for the meet to be held for the first time in India. Four other countries  South Korea, Singapore, Australia and New Zealand  are also expected to take part.  India finished runners-up in the last edition of the meet held in South Korea 2005. 
